- What designs work on short coffin nails specifically (not just long)?
- Which style is easiest to DIY vs. which needs a nail tech?
- What makes coffin nail designs different from just putting the same design on any other shape?

*Missing Semantic Territory:*
- Skin-tone-aware design recommendations
- Occasion-mapped design categories
- Design difficulty ratings (DIY vs. salon)
- Shape-design synergy (why certain designs work uniquely well on the flat coffin tip vs. other shapes)
- 2026-specific aesthetic context (what's elevated vs. what reads as dated now)

*Audience Blind Spots in Current Results:*
- No one explains how the coffin shape itself changes how a design looks compared to oval or square
- Skin tone coverage is limited and usually buried or tokenistic
- Occasion-specific guidance is vague or absent — "works for any occasion" is not helpful when you're choosing for a specific event

**Our Strategic Approach:**
Organise this post around the decision the reader is actually trying to make: which design suits my style, my occasion, and my vibe — not just a random scroll of options. Lead with the inspirational pull of the visuals, but layer editorial curation that makes every section feel chosen, not aggregated. Use the unique flat tip of the coffin shape as a narrative thread — these designs work *because* of the shape, not despite it.

